snippet: While home sales are projected to rise this year, economists doubt that they will return to a more typical pace.
abstract: National Assn of Home Builders/Wells Fargo builder sentiment index slips to 55 in February from January level of 57, indicating slight decline in sales prospects and buyer traffic; index nonetheless shows optimism ahead of spring buying season.
lead_paragraph: While home sales are projected to rise this year, economists doubt that they will return to a more typical pace.

headline.main: Homebuilder Sentiment Slips, but Still Points to Optimism for Spring Sales
headline.print_headline: Homebuilder Sentiment Slips, but Still Points to Optimism for Spring Sales
